  - TOKEN_USAGE: Prompt=41479, Gen=743
  - TOOL_CALL: create_or_update_file({"file_path": "generated_prompt_file/commit_changed.txt", "content": "--- 【HAFix ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS】 ---\nSuspect SHA: b51c61e8de9ec1523f642431d71ce406b50b1f0a\nRoot Cause Chain: Commit b51c61e8d bumped Go from 1.24.0 to 1.25.0 in go.mod, which changed how the Go toolchain is distributed (as a module under GOMODCACHE). The go-118-fuzz-build tool creates an overlay file that replaces testing/fuzz.go in the Go toolchain, but Go 1.25+ forbids overlay replacements beneath GOMODCACHE (/root/go/pkg/mod), causing the build to fail with \"Files beneath GOMODCACHE must not be replaced.\"\nAttribution: DOWNSTREAM\nTarget Fix Path: /home/senchen/temp/fix_build_agent/oss-fuzz/projects/cert-manager\nKey Evidence: The build log shows: \"go: overlay contains a replacement for /root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/src/testing/fuzz.go. Files beneath GOMODCACHE (/root/go/pkg/mod) must not be replaced.\" This is an OSS-Fuzz infrastructure incompatibility between go-118-fuzz-build's overlay mechanism and Go 1.25+'s toolchain-as-module distribution model. The fix should either (1) patch the build.sh to set GOTOOLCHAIN=go1.24.0 to force an older compatible toolchain, or (2) update the go-118-fuzz-build tool to handle Go 1.25+ toolchain modules correctly.\n"})
