  - STATE_UPDATE: {'commit_analysis_result': 'The HAFix analysis is complete. Let me summarize the findings.\n\n---\n\n## HAFix Root Cause Analysis Summary\n\n### Phase 1: Dynamic Clue Mining\n- **Clue Type**: `time_window` (Fallback Mode - no error_date provided)\n- **Error**: `go: overlay contains a replacement for /root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/src/testing/fuzz.go. Files beneath GOMODCACHE (/root/go/pkg/mod) must not be replaced.`\n\n### Phase 2-3: Chain-of-Evidence Synthesis\n**Top 3 Suspects Analyzed:**\n1. **e60d148b9** (HEAD) - `fix(deps): update github.com/onsi deps` - Only changes test/e2e deps, not the root cause\n2. **b51c61e8d** - `fix(deps): update misc go deps` - **Bumped Go from 1.24.0 to 1.25.0** - This is the commit that introduced the incompatible Go version\n3. **1d5755d81** - `fix(deps): update module github.com/hashicorp/vault/sdk to v0.25.1` - Bumped Go from 1.25.0 to 1.25.7\n\n### Phase 4: Attribution Decision\n- **Attribution**: **DOWNSTREAM** (Config/Infrastructure)\n- **Reason**: The `go-118-fuzz-build` tool (part of OSS-Fuzz infrastructure) creates an overlay file that replaces `testing/fuzz.go` in the Go toolchain. Starting from Go 1.25, the Go toolchain is distributed as a module under GOMODCACHE, and Go 1.25+ forbids overlay replacements beneath GOMODCACHE. This is an infrastructure incompatibility, not a source code bug.\n- **Target Fix Path**: `/home/senchen/temp/fix_build_agent/oss-fuzz/projects/cert-manager`\n- **Suggested Fix**: Either (1) patch `build.sh` to set `GOTOOLCHAIN=go1.24.0` to force an older compatible toolchain, or (2) update the `go-118-fuzz-build` tool to handle Go 1.25+ toolchain modules correctly.'}
