  - TOKEN_USAGE: Prompt=139862, Gen=314
  - STATE_UPDATE: {'patch_application_result': 'The patch has been successfully applied and state saved with an [AGENT_FIX] marker.\n\n**Summary of the fix applied to `build.sh`:**\n\nThe build was failing with:\n```\ngo: overlay contains a replacement for /root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/src/testing/fuzz.go. Files beneath GOMODCACHE (/root/go/pkg/mod) must not be replaced.\n```\n\n**Root Cause:** Go 1.25+ stores the toolchain as a module under GOMODCACHE. The `go-118-fuzz-build` tool creates an overlay that replaces `$GOROOT/src/testing/fuzz.go`, but Go 1.25+ forbids overlay replacements beneath GOMODCACHE.\n\n**Fix:** After `go mod tidy` downloads the correct Go toolchain to GOMODCACHE, the build script now:\n1. Gets the GOROOT path (which points to the toolchain module under GOMODCACHE)\n2. Copies the toolchain from GOMODCACHE to `/root/.go` (the local Go installation directory)\n3. Sets `GOTOOLCHAIN=local` so subsequent Go commands use the local installation with GOROOT at `/root/.go` (outside GOMODCACHE)\n\nThis allows the `go-118-fuzz-build` overlay mechanism to work correctly because the overlay target path is no longer under GOMODCACHE.'}
